# 🚀 Dashboard Enhancement Features — Implementation Plan

> **Goal**: Add three premium intelligence features to the Jurist AI Overview dashboard **without any backend changes** and without breaking existing functionality.

---

## What We're Building

```mermaid
graph TD
  A["Analysis Result<br/>(already in frontend state)"] --> B["🎯 AI Narrative Verdict"]
  A --> C["📊 Severity Distribution"]
  A --> D["🔍 NLP vs Deep AI Transparency"]
  B --> E["OverviewPage.jsx"]
  C --> E
  D --> E
```

All three features consume data **already returned by the backend** — no API changes needed.

---

## Feature 1 — AI Narrative Verdict (3-Sentence Summary)

### Concept
After analysis completes, auto-fire a chat API call asking for a concise 3-sentence "verdict" of the document. Display it as a premium card at the top of the Overview page.

### Data Flow

```mermaid
sequenceDiagram
  participant App as App.jsx
  participant API as /chat endpoint
  participant UI as OverviewPage

  App->>App: Analysis completes (pollAnalysisResults)
  App->>API: POST /chat { session_id, message: "verdict prompt" }
  API-->>App: { reply: "3-sentence verdict" }
  App->>UI: Pass narrativeVerdict prop
  UI->>UI: Render verdict card
```

### Implementation Details

#### [MODIFY] [App.jsx](file:///home/aarush_linux/projects/PBL/frontend/src/App.jsx)

**Add state:**
```jsx
const [narrativeVerdict, setNarrativeVerdict] = useState(null);
const [isVerdictLoading, setIsVerdictLoading] = useState(false);
```

**Add function (after [sendChat](file:///home/aarush_linux/projects/PBL/frontend/src/App.jsx#479-528)):**
```jsx
const fetchNarrativeVerdict = async (targetSessionId) => {
  if (!targetSessionId || !token) return;
  setIsVerdictLoading(true);
  try {
    const prompt = `In exactly 3 sentences, give a plain-English verdict of this document's risk profile. 
Sentence 1: Overall safety assessment (safe/moderate/dangerous). 
Sentence 2: The single most critical risk and why it matters. 
Sentence 3: Your recommendation (sign as-is / negotiate changes / avoid).
Do NOT use bullet points, just 3 flowing sentences.`;

    const res = await fetchWithRetry(`${API}/chat`, {
      method: 'POST',
      headers: {
        'Content-Type': 'application/json',
        'Authorization': `Bearer ${token}`
      },
      body: JSON.stringify({ session_id: targetSessionId, message: prompt, history: [] })
    });
    if (res.ok) {
      const data = await res.json();
      setNarrativeVerdict(data.reply || null);
    }
  } catch (err) {
    console.error('Verdict fetch failed:', err);
  } finally {
    setIsVerdictLoading(false);
  }
};
```

**Trigger it in two places:**

1. In [pollAnalysisResults](file:///home/aarush_linux/projects/PBL/frontend/src/App.jsx#321-367) — when `data.status === 'complete'`, add:
   ```jsx
   fetchNarrativeVerdict(jobId);
   ```

2. In [openHistoryAnalysis](file:///home/aarush_linux/projects/PBL/frontend/src/App.jsx#273-318) — after setting `analysisResult`, add:
   ```jsx
   fetchNarrativeVerdict(data.job_id);
   ```

**Clear it on new analysis:**
```jsx
// In startAnalysis(), before setIsProcessing(true):
setNarrativeVerdict(null);
```

**Pass to OverviewPage:**
```jsx
<OverviewPage
  // ...existing props
  narrativeVerdict={narrativeVerdict}
  isVerdictLoading={isVerdictLoading}
/>
```

---

