## Feature 2 — Severity Distribution Histogram

### Concept
Replace the single "Avg Severity" number in the 5-stat grid with a **visual histogram** showing clause distribution by severity tier: Minor (0–2), Moderate (2–5), Serious (5–8), Critical (8–12), Fatal (12+).

### Data Source
Per-clause `severity_score` is already computed in [analyze_document()](file:///home/aarush_linux/projects/PBL/backend/analysis/analyzer.py#129-259) via [compute_clause_severity()](file:///home/aarush_linux/projects/PBL/backend/analysis/analyzer.py#39-56) and stored on each clause object. The frontend already has `analysisResult.clauses` in state.

> [!IMPORTANT]
> `severity_score` is only set on **risky** clauses (ones that went through LLM). Non-risky (NLP-filtered) clauses have `severity_score = 0` or undefined.
> We compute the bins from risky clauses only, then show "NLP Cleared" as a separate green bin.

### Implementation Details

#### [MODIFY] [OverviewPage.jsx](file:///home/aarush_linux/projects/PBL/frontend/src/components/OverviewPage.jsx)

**Add severity distribution computation (after existing `useMemo` blocks):**

```jsx
const severityDistribution = React.useMemo(() => {
  if (!Array.isArray(analysisResult?.clauses)) return [];
  
  const bins = [
    { label: 'Minor',    range: '0–2',   color: '#22c55e', count: 0 },
    { label: 'Moderate', range: '2–5',   color: '#f59e0b', count: 0 },
    { label: 'Serious',  range: '5–8',   color: '#f97316', count: 0 },
    { label: 'Critical', range: '8–12',  color: '#ef4444', count: 0 },
    { label: 'Fatal',    range: '12+',   color: '#dc2626', count: 0 },
  ];

  analysisResult.clauses.forEach(clause => {
    if (!clause.is_risky) return; // skip NLP-cleared
    const sev = clause.severity_score || 0;
    if (sev <= 2)       bins[0].count++;
    else if (sev <= 5)  bins[1].count++;
    else if (sev <= 8)  bins[2].count++;
    else if (sev <= 12) bins[3].count++;
    else                bins[4].count++;
  });

  return bins;
}, [analysisResult]);

const maxBinCount = Math.max(...severityDistribution.map(b => b.count), 1);
```

**Replace the "Avg Severity" stat card (line ~216) with a severity histogram card:**

Change the stats array from:
```jsx
{ label: 'Avg Severity', value: avgSeverity.toFixed(2), icon: TrendingUp, color: 'text-amber-400' },
```
To:
```jsx
{ label: 'Avg Severity', value: avgSeverity.toFixed(2), icon: TrendingUp, color: 'text-amber-400', isHistogram: true },
```

Then update the rendering at ~line 220 to check `isHistogram`:

```jsx
{stat.isHistogram ? (
  <div key={i} className="glass-card p-6 col-span-2 hover:border-white/20 transition-all">
    <div className="flex items-center justify-between mb-4">
      <div className="flex items-center gap-2">
        <TrendingUp size={16} className="text-amber-400" />
        <span className="text-sm text-white/50 uppercase">Severity Distribution</span>
      </div>
      <span className="text-lg font-bold text-white">
        avg {avgSeverity.toFixed(1)}
      </span>
    </div>
    <div className="flex items-end gap-2 h-24">
      {severityDistribution.map((bin, j) => (
        <div key={j} className="flex-1 flex flex-col items-center gap-1">
          <span className="text-[10px] text-white/50 font-medium">
            {bin.count > 0 ? bin.count : ''}
          </span>
          <div
            className="w-full rounded-t-md transition-all duration-700"
            style={{
              height: `${bin.count > 0 ? Math.max(8, (bin.count / maxBinCount) * 100) : 4}%`,
              backgroundColor: bin.count > 0 ? bin.color : 'rgba(255,255,255,0.05)',
            }}
          />
          <span className="text-[9px] text-white/40 uppercase leading-none text-center">
            {bin.label}
          </span>
        </div>
      ))}
    </div>
  </div>
) : (
  // ...existing stat card rendering
)}
```

> [!TIP]
> The histogram takes `col-span-2` in the grid to have room for 5 bars. You'll need to adjust the grid from `grid-cols-5` to `grid-cols-6` and give the other 4 regular cards `col-span-1` each. Or alternatively, move the histogram to a separate row below.

**Alternative (simpler, no grid changes):** Keep the stat card as-is but add a small inline sparkline histogram inside it:

```jsx
// Inside the existing stat card for Avg Severity:
<div className="flex items-end gap-1 mt-2 h-8">
  {severityDistribution.map((bin, j) => (
    <div
      key={j}
      className="flex-1 rounded-t-sm transition-all duration-500"
      title={`${bin.label}: ${bin.count} clauses`}
      style={{
        height: `${bin.count > 0 ? Math.max(15, (bin.count / maxBinCount) * 100) : 8}%`,
        backgroundColor: bin.count > 0 ? bin.color : 'rgba(255,255,255,0.05)',
      }}
    />
  ))}
</div>
```

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Recommended approach:** Use the **separate card** (first option) for maximum visual impact. Add a new row below the 5-stat grid with the histogram + the transparency card side by side.

