## Feature 3 — NLP vs Deep AI Transparency Breakdown

### Concept
Show users **how** the analysis happened: how many clauses were quickly filtered by the NLP engine ("fast scan") vs. how many went through the Cerebras/LLM deep analysis ("deep AI"). This builds trust by showing the "thinking" behind the analysis.

### Data Source
Already available in `analysisResult`:
- `total_clauses` — total count
- `skipped_llm_count` — number filtered by fast NLP (did NOT go to LLM)
- `risky_clause_count` — number flagged as risky
- Per-clause `skipped_llm: true/false` — exact breakdown

### Implementation Details

#### [MODIFY] [OverviewPage.jsx](file:///home/aarush_linux/projects/PBL/frontend/src/components/OverviewPage.jsx)

**Add transparency computation:**

```jsx
const analysisTransparency = React.useMemo(() => {
  if (!analysisResult) return null;
  const total = analysisResult.total_clauses || 0;
  const nlpFiltered = analysisResult.skipped_llm_count || 0;
  const deepAnalyzed = total - nlpFiltered;
  const riskyFound = analysisResult.risky_clause_count || 0;
  const safeFromDeep = deepAnalyzed - riskyFound;

  return {
    total,
    nlpFiltered,                              // Quick NLP pass — determined safe
    deepAnalyzed,                             // Sent to Cerebras LLM
    riskyFound,                               // LLM flagged as risky
    safeFromDeep,                             // LLM cleared as safe
    nlpPercent: total > 0 ? ((nlpFiltered / total) * 100).toFixed(0) : 0,
    deepPercent: total > 0 ? ((deepAnalyzed / total) * 100).toFixed(0) : 0,
  };
}, [analysisResult]);
```

**Add transparency card (alongside the histogram, in a new `grid grid-cols-2` row):**

```jsx
{/* Analysis Transparency */}
{analysisTransparency && (
  <div className="glass-card p-6">
    <h3 className="text-base font-semibold text-white mb-4 flex items-center gap-2">
