## Safety Guarantees

> [!CAUTION]
> These rules ensure zero breakage:

1. **All data already exists** — `severity_score`, `skipped_llm`, `is_risky` are already in every clause object. No new API calls except the chat verdict (which is a standard chat message).
2. **Verdict is fire-and-forget** — if the chat API fails, the card simply doesn't render (`narrativeVerdict` stays `null`). No blocking.
3. **All new UI is additive** — new cards are inserted into the existing grid, no existing cards removed (Avg Severity stat card stays, histogram is a new addition alongside it).
4. **No props contract changes** — [OverviewPage](file:///home/aarush_linux/projects/PBL/frontend/src/components/OverviewPage.jsx#8-425) gets two optional new props (`narrativeVerdict`, `isVerdictLoading`). Backwards compatible.
5. **No backend changes** — nothing in [main.py](file:///home/aarush_linux/projects/PBL/backend/main.py), [analyzer.py](file:///home/aarush_linux/projects/PBL/backend/analysis/analyzer.py), or any Python file is touched.

