## Verification Plan

### Browser Testing

1. **Dev server** is already running at `http://localhost:5173` via `npm run dev`
2. Open the app in the browser
3. Run a new analysis on any document (URL or paste text)
4. After analysis completes, verify on the Overview page:
   - [ ] AI Verdict card appears with loading skeleton, then fills with 3-sentence text
   - [ ] Severity histogram renders with colored bars per tier
   - [ ] "How We Analyzed" transparency card shows NLP vs Deep AI split with correct numbers
5. Navigate to a **history item** → verify verdict auto-loads for that too
6. Verify **all existing features** still work:
   - [ ] Score gauge renders correctly
   - [ ] Stat cards show correct values
   - [ ] Risk Profile and Radar chart still render
   - [ ] Key Risk Factors cards still functional
   - [ ] Navigation between Overview / Clauses / Compare / Reports works
   - [ ] Chat popup still works

### Number Validation
- `NLP Filtered + Deep Analyzed = Total Clauses` (must always hold)
- `AI Cleared + Flagged Risky = Deep Analyzed` (must always hold)
- Histogram bin counts should sum to `risky_clause_count`

### Edge Cases
- Analysis with **0 risky clauses** — histogram should show all-zero bars, transparency should show all NLP-filtered
- Very short document (1–2 clauses) — layout should not break
- Chat API failure — verdict card should simply not appear (no error toast)
